<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="562" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/117: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-24T17:00:00-05:00">April 24, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>135. Department’s #2, January 2, 6 p.m. Commander-in-Chief Asiatic Fleet
                            is being asked by Secretary of Navy for his opinion as to advisability
                            under present conditions of withdrawing all or part of marines now
                            stationed in Shanghai. Department would like to have your opinion
                            regarding this. Opinion here is that marines should be evacuated unless
                            there is some controlling reason why they should remain.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
